To ensure evaluation quality and provide teams with ample preparation time, all registered teams
must complete the online submission of the following materials within 20,March 7p.m. The
submitted materials will serve as the basis for the judges' preliminary understanding of the
projects and will be factored into the comprehensive evaluation.
1. Detailed Project Description Document
Word Count Requirement: No fewer than 300 words (can be in Chinese or English).
Content Requirements: The document should be well-structured and include at least the following
sections:
Project Overview: A one-sentence summary of the project's core value.
Inspiration: Why was this direction chosen? What specific problem does it aim to solve, or what
need does it address?
What it does: Explain the main functions of the project. How do users interact with it?
How we built it: Describe the technology stack, tools, algorithms, etc
Individual contributions: Explain how the work was divided among teammates
Challenges we ran into: Explain any challenges your team ran into along the way
Accomplishments that we’re proud of: What are the innovative aspects compared to existing
solutions?
What we learned: Explain what your team learned throughout the process
What’s next for our project: What positive changes could the project bring to target users, the
community, or society? Given more time, in what ways could you further expand on your
project?
Format Requirement: PDF format.
File naming: TeamLeaderName_ProjectName_ Description.pdf
2. Project Demo Video
Duration Requirement: No longer than 5 minutes.
Content Requirements: The video should intuitively demonstrate the core functions or
conceptual presentation of the work, accompanied by a brief explanation.
Software Projects: Can be a screen recording showcasing the interface interaction and core
operational processes, with voice-over or subtitles.
Hardware Projects: Can be a live-action video showing the hardware appearance, operational
status, and actual usage scenarios, possibly combined with operational demonstrations.
Concept Proposal Projects (not yet implemented): Can be a concept demo animation,
prototype interaction simulation, or a recorded presentation combined with PPT to clearly convey
the design concept.
Quality Suggestions:
Clear, stable picture with adequate lighting, and clear audio. Commentary can be in Chinese or
English.
The video should start by displaying the project name and team information, and may end with a
team appearance or acknowledgments to showcase team spirit.
Avoid lengthy introductions; get straight to the core functionality demonstration.
Format Requirement: MP4 format, file size is recommended not to exceed 500MB.
File naming: TeamLeaderName_ProjectName_Demo.mp4.
3. Code Repository Link
Requirement: If the project has existing code implementation, please provide a publicly
accessible code repository link (e.g., GitHub, Gitee, etc.). For pure hardware projects, a repository
link containing design files, circuit diagrams, and other resources can be provided.
Repository Standard Suggestions:
1、Repository Name: It is recommended to name the repository HackMITChina2026.
2、The repository should include a clear README.md file, introducing the project background,
features, installation/running guide, dependencies, etc.
3、The code structure should be clear, with necessary comments. Key algorithms or modules can
be explained separately.
4 、For hardware designs, it may include schematics, PCB files, 3D models, bill of materials
(BOM), etc.
5、Keep the repository tidy by deleting temporary files and unnecessary binary files.
6 、Submission Method: Directly fill in the repository URL in the submission form. If the
repository is private, please ensure temporary access is granted during the evaluation period (e.g.,
by inviting judge accounts or generating a temporary link).
Software Code Reference: GitHub - Antoine-Lafrance/HackMIT
Hardware Code Reference: GitHub - S-Sigdel/SenseNav
The submitted materials must include: the project description document, the project demo
video, and a text file containing the GitHub repository address.
If any of the required materials are missing, the committee reserves the right to assess the specific
situation and determine the team's eligibility to continue in the competition.